P(L)=\frac{3\color{gainsboro}{00}}{8\color{gainsboro}{00}},\; P(L')=\frac{5\color{gainsboro}{00}}{8\color{gainsboro}{00}},\; P(N\mid L) = \frac{2\color{gainsboro}{00}}{3\color{gainsboro}{00}},\; P(N\mid L') = \frac{2\color{gainsboro}{00}}{5\color{gainsboro}{00}}
P(X\cap Y)=P(X)\cdot P(Y\mid X)
P(X\cup Y) = 1 - P(X'\cap Y')
P(L\cap N) = P(L)\cdot P(N \mid L)
